    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Mexico, an ejido is a communal land-holding institution that allocates land to a farming community for collective use. Historically, this system of communal land tenure replaced the feudal system after the Mexican Revolution of 1910.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
